caption.text:
When I said I ever went through the steepest rack railway, I wasn‚Äôt playing around.

Took this from across the summit station. Legit.

Sometimes when you're too focus on getting the perfect angle you tend to step forward and backward to find the perfect point of view. I ain't no pro picture takers but I'm aware that I have a pretty interesting perspective. Okay, calm your horses‚Äìlet‚Äôs not get cocky.

Anywhooo, there's gonna be times when people actually crossed in front of your camera as if they're doing a catwalk and you're just standing there like, ‚ÄúAye! Can‚Äôt you see I‚Äôm trying to capture a moment that might not appear ever again? Unless it's a building. It's not going anywhere, of course. But still. You're the bad guy. Move.‚Äù Am I right or am I right?

But during my stay in Paris, people actually cares about that. What pleased me the most was when I actually let them walked first, they flashed a smile and said, ‚ÄúMerci.‚Äù I know it's not that big of deal but for me it's a huge deal. Smile was plastered on my face.

The bottom line is be polite. Lol. Nah. That ain‚Äôt no scientific statement.

The bottom line is you can find happiness in the simplest thing of life. It doesn't have to be those luxury things the world is often offering nowadays.

#LifeLesson #WiseNight
